nodeTypes.comment: A local variable
nodeTypes.name: LOCAL

nodeTypes.comment: A comment
nodeTypes.name: COMMENT

nodeTypes.comment: A method/function/procedure
nodeTypes.name: METHOD

nodeTypes.comment: A string tag
nodeTypes.name: TAG

nodeTypes.comment: A literal value assigned to an ANNOTATION_PARAMETER
nodeTypes.name: ANNOTATION_LITERAL

nodeTypes.comment: This node represents a formal parameter going towards the callee side
nodeTypes.name: METHOD_PARAMETER_IN

nodeTypes.comment: This node represents a namespace as a whole whereas the NAMESPACE_BLOCK is used for each grouping occurrence of a namespace in code. Single representing NAMESPACE node is required for easier navigation in the query language
nodeTypes.name: NAMESPACE

nodeTypes.comment: Represents the binding of a LOCAL or METHOD_PARAMETER_IN into the closure of a method
nodeTypes.name: CLOSURE_BINDING

nodeTypes.comment: A language-specific node
nodeTypes.name: UNKNOWN

nodeTypes.comment: Formal annotation parameter
nodeTypes.name: ANNOTATION_PARAMETER

nodeTypes.comment: Member of a class struct or union
nodeTypes.name: MEMBER

nodeTypes.comment: A method instance which always has to reference a method and may have type argument children if the referred to method is a template
nodeTypes.name: METHOD_INST

nodeTypes.comment: Configuration file contents. Might be in use by a framework
nodeTypes.name: CONFIG_FILE

nodeTypes.comment: Node to save meta data about the graph on its properties. Exactly one node of this type per graph
nodeTypes.name: META_DATA

nodeTypes.comment: A return instruction
nodeTypes.name: RETURN

nodeTypes.comment: Attribute of a DOM node
nodeTypes.name: DOM_ATTRIBUTE

nodeTypes.comment: Argument for a TYPE_PARAMETER that belongs to a TYPE. It binds another TYPE to a TYPE_PARAMETER
nodeTypes.name: TYPE_ARGUMENT

nodeTypes.comment: A node that represents which field is accessed in a <operator>.fieldAccess, in e.g. obj.field. The CODE part is used for human display and matching to MEMBER nodes. The CANONICAL_NAME is used for dataflow tracking; typically both coincide. However, suppose that two fields foo and bar are a C-style union; then CODE refers to whatever the programmer wrote (obj.foo or obj.bar), but both share the same CANONICAL_NAME (e.g. GENERATED_foo_bar)
nodeTypes.name: FIELD_IDENTIFIER

nodeTypes.comment: A node in a Document Object Model (Tree) as obtained from, e.g., an HTML parser
nodeTypes.name: DOM_NODE

nodeTypes.comment: A reference to a namespace
nodeTypes.name: NAMESPACE_BLOCK

nodeTypes.comment: Initialization construct for arrays
nodeTypes.name: ARRAY_INITIALIZER

nodeTypes.comment: A method annotation
nodeTypes.name: ANNOTATION

nodeTypes.comment: An arbitrary identifier/reference
nodeTypes.name: IDENTIFIER

nodeTypes.comment: Node representing a source file. Often also the AST root
nodeTypes.name: FILE

nodeTypes.comment: This node represents a dependency
nodeTypes.name: DEPENDENCY

nodeTypes.comment: This node records what package prefix is most common to all analysed classes in the CPG
nodeTypes.name: PACKAGE_PREFIX

nodeTypes.comment: An implicit call site hidden in a method indicated by METHOD_MAP policy entries
nodeTypes.name: IMPLICIT_CALL

nodeTypes.comment: Indicates the usage of a framework. E.g. java spring. The name key is one of the values from frameworks list
nodeTypes.name: FRAMEWORK

nodeTypes.comment: A modifier, e.g., static, public, private
nodeTypes.name: MODIFIER

nodeTypes.comment: A control structure such as if, while, or for
nodeTypes.name: CONTROL_STRUCTURE

nodeTypes.comment: A structuring block in the AST
nodeTypes.name: BLOCK

nodeTypes.comment: Data used by a framework
nodeTypes.name: FRAMEWORK_DATA

nodeTypes.comment: Literal/Constant
nodeTypes.name: LITERAL

nodeTypes.comment: A formal method return
nodeTypes.name: METHOD_RETURN

nodeTypes.comment: This node represents a formal parameter going towards the caller side
nodeTypes.name: METHOD_PARAMETER_OUT

nodeTypes.comment: A type which always has to reference a type declaration and may have type argument children if the referred to type declaration is a template
nodeTypes.name: TYPE

nodeTypes.comment: Reference to a method instance
nodeTypes.name: METHOD_REF

nodeTypes.comment: A type declaration
nodeTypes.name: TYPE_DECL

containedNodes.comment: This field also holds tags for output parameters and return parameters

nodeTypes.comment: A (method)-call
nodeTypes.name: CALL

nodeTypes.comment: Type parameter of TYPE_DECL or METHOD
nodeTypes.name: TYPE_PARAMETER

nodeTypes.comment: Multiple tags
nodeTypes.name: TAGS

nodeTypes.comment: Assignment of annotation argument to annotation parameter
nodeTypes.name: ANNOTATION_PARAMETER_ASSIGN

nodeTypes.comment: A binding of a METHOD into a TYPE_DECL
nodeTypes.name: BINDING
